    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Numbers have two main types\n",
        "- Integers are whole numbers: -14, -2, 0, 1, 100, 401233\n",
        "- Floating Point Numbers have decimal parts: -2.5, 0.0, 98.6, 14.0<br/>\n",
        "There are other number types - they are variations on float and integer"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "C2u0mXyhtlbZ"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "quDNk2aks6ZP",
        "outputId": "331faf1a-7fea-4008-b7dd-e44814be91a9"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "<class 'int'>\n",
            "<class 'float'>\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "xx = 1\n",
        "print(type(xx))\n",
        "temp = 98.6\n",
        "print(type(temp))"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Type Conversions\n",
        "- When you put an integer and floating point in an expression, the integer is implicitly converted to a float\n",
        "- You can control this with the built-in functions `int()` and `float()`"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Kc139s1evOda"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "print(float(99) + 100) #force converting this into a float number\n",
        "\n",
        "i = 42\n",
        "print(type(i))\n",
        "\n",
        "#manipulate i into float\n",
        "f = float(i)\n",
        "print(f)\n",
        "print(type(f))"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "M_1t0NGCvTSD",
        "outputId": "08a59997-18ea-4cef-f9e5-9c870e046cca"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "199.0\n",
            "<class 'int'>\n",
            "42.0\n",
            "<class 'float'>\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Integer Division\n",
        "Integer division produces a floating point result in Python 3 and later."
        "Division in Python always produces a floating point number"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ZHFt8QZTwMiO"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "print(10 / 2)\n",
        "print(9 / 2)\n",
        "print(99 / 100)\n",
        "print(10.0 / 2.0)\n",
        "print(99.0 / 100.0)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "4RIRDxyIwnkv",
        "outputId": "9f3d5577-f3ba-472c-f10b-e19d5b267020"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "5.0\n",
            "4.5\n",
            "0.99\n",
            "5.0\n",
            "0.99\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## String Conversions\n",
        "- You can also use `int()` and `float()` to convert between strings and integers"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7802vgh2xCZl"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "sval = '123'\n",
        "print(type(sval))\n",
        "\n",
        "#convert string to int\n",
        "ival = int(sval)\n",
        "print(type(ival))\n",
        "print(ival)\n",
        "print(ival + 1)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "yicy2EqW1DBk",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "91d261ba-0095-47a1-a362-5a78bc95dea9"
      },
      "execution_count": 6,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "<class 'str'>\n",
            "<class 'int'>\n",
            "123\n",
            "124\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "- You will  get an error if you try to do arithmetical operation to string variable"
