      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## User Input\n",
        "- We can instruct Python to pause and read data from the user using the `input()` function\n",
        "- The `input()` function returns a string"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "k2cFVw3G3BWX"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "With Space"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "66DqONy73xZ-"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "nam = input('Who are you?')\n",
        "print('Welcome', nam)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "se6HNARc3Qfc",
        "outputId": "31065d63-f643-4b87-dd5e-47696d215dd2"
      },
      "execution_count": 10,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Who are you?Chuck\n",
            "Welcome Chuck\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
